				<h2 class="prj-title">La Ciudad Ligera</h2>
				
				<p class="para-text-2 prj-deets-2">
					<span class="prj-deet">Tags</span> poster, 2018 <br>
					<span class="prj-deet hanging">Client</span> open call <br>
					<span class="prj-deet hanging">Jury selection</span>
					<img class="grid-img pdd-img" src="images/madrid-grafica-2017-badge.png" width="90px" style="padding-top: 5px">
				</p>
				
               
				<p class="text first-p">
				The first edition of <strong>Madrid Gráfica</strong>, a graphic design festival organized by the Madrid Design Association, held an open call for posters about the cities of the future. Making use of an expression coined by Italian industrial designer <strong>Carmelo di Bartolo</strong>, <em>«The Light City»</em> (<em>«La Ciudad Ligera»</em> in Spanish) became the motto for the open call, as well as mandatory content in the posters.
				
				</p>
				<p class="text">	
					
				The jury, composed of <strong>Ivan Chermayeff</strong>, <strong>Mirko Ilic</strong>, <strong>Alejandro Magallanes</strong>, <strong>Pekka Loiri</strong>, <strong>Alain Le Quernec</strong> and <strong>di Bartolo</strong>, selected 100 posters to be exhibited at the Paseo del Prado and at Plaza Sanchéz Bustillo, in front of the Reina Sofía Museum, in Madrid.
				
				</p>
                
